text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia lobulata, common name Chiddarcooping Wattle, is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to a small area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The erect open shrub typically grows to a height of 1 to 2 metres (3 to 7 ft). It blooms in July and produces yellow flowers.
